               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 3 items (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of works relating to the saint, <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn al-Bukhārī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, known as the <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht</persName> (d. 785/1384). 
Volume not dated; items a and b dated (19 Ramaz̤ān 1130/16 August 1718.) separately; items share similar origins, paper and scribal hand. 
Contemporary and later illuminated headpieces at the beginning of the first two items. Gilt and coloured rulings throughout. 
Distinct scribal nastaʿlīq and taʿlīq. Catchwords often partially cropped. 
Pencil foliation. 
Occasional annotations and corrections in margins. 
Lacking original binding. 
Leather binding damaged (tooled brown leather ornamented with medallions and painted rulings over flexible pasteboards, doublures stripped away exposing inner matter), labelled. 
Folios unbound; cropped, stained, wormholes, later repairs. 
The volume is strongly scented with spice. 
Condition very fragile. 
Seals of later owners. 

                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1107-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="102v">ff. 1v-102v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Hagiographic treatise collecting anecdotes relating to the saints, <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Shaykh Sayyid Jalāl al-Dīn al-Ḥusayn [al-Ḥusaynī] al-Bukhārī</persName> the <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Makhdūm-i Jahāniyān</persName> (d. 785/1384), his son <persName key="person_f7602" role="subject">Shaykh Sayyid Maḥmūd Nāṣir al-Dīn</persName>, his son <persName key="person_f7529" role="subject">Sayyid Ḥāmid Kabīr</persName>, his son <persName key="person_f7603" role="subject">Shaykh Sayyid Rukn al-Dīn Abū al-Fatḥ</persName>. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The author, describing himself as a disciple of <persName key="person_f7529" role="oth">Shaykh Sayyid Ḥāmid Kabīr</persName>, has not been identified by name within the text. However, Storey suggests the author may be <persName key="person_f7442" role="att">Najm al-Dīn Yūsuf ibn Rukn al-Dīn Muḥammad Niʿmat Allāh Gardīzī</persName>, author of the <title>Awrād-i Yūsufī</title>. 


                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 102v): completed by <persName key="person_f7330" role="scr">Muḥammad Afz̤al</persName> for <persName key="person_f7001" role="pat">[Sayyid] Shāh Lillāhī</persName>, 19 Ramaz̤ān 1130/16 August 1718. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Severely oxidised and faded illuminated sarlawḥ in a contemporary style of floral arabesque around interlocking brackets, ʿunvān enclosing the opening basmalah on folio 1v. Gilt and coloured rulings marking the jadval of the main text. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22200">Maḥbūbīyah</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1107-item2">
                     <locus from="103v" to="174v">ff. 103v-174v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7534">Sayyid Maḥmūd Bangālī</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22201">Sayr'nāmah</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Account of the four-decade-long travels in the Middle East of the Ṣūfī saint, <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Abū ʿAbd Allāh Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn al-Bukhārī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, known as the <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht</persName> (d. 785/1384), compiled under his supervision by his disciple, <persName key="person_f7534" role="ctb">Sayyid Maḥmūd Bangālī</persName>. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 174v): completed by <persName key="person_f7330" role="scr">Muḥammad Afz̤al</persName>, 1130/1718.
 
                        </p>
                        <p>Pale painted illuminated sarlawḥ in a later style of floral arabesque within a half-turunj, ʿunvān enclosing the opening basmalah on folio 103v. Gilt and coloured rulings marking the jadval of the main text. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1107-item3">
                     <locus from="174v" to="175v">ff. 174v-175v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt from an unidentified hagiographic source reporting the testimony of a <persName key="person_f7265" role="ant">Mawlānā Bahrām</persName> on the death and burial of the Ṣūfī saint, <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Abū ʿAbd Allāh Jalāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn al-Bukhārī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, known as the <persName key="person_91095241" role="subject">Makhdūm Jahāniyān Jahān Gasht</persName> (d. 785/1384). 

                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. Completed by the same hand as that found in items a-b, and probably in the same year. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
